cnLecsMpoaMpcTable.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcTable
cnLecsMpoaMpcTable.description: The Bay Networks proprietary LECS MPC Table. This table contains configuration information for all LECS Mpoa Mpcs this agent manages.

cnLecsMpoaMpcEntry.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcEntry
cnLecsMpoaMpcEntry.description: Each entry contains LECS MPC information for all LECS this agent manages.

cnLecsMpoaMpcIndex.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcIndex
cnLecsMpoaMpcIndex.description: A value which uniquely identifies this conceptual row in the cnLecsMpoaMpcTable.

cnLecsMpoaMpcRowStatus.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcRowStatus
cnLecsMpoaMpcRowStatus.description: This object allows creation and deletion of Lecs MPOA Clients. Within each conceptual cnLecsMpoaMpcTable row, writable objects may be modified, regardless of the value of cnLecsMpoaMpcRowStatus.

cnLecsMpoaMpcCtrlAtmAddr.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcCtrlAtmAddr
cnLecsMpoaMpcCtrlAtmAddr.description: The MPC's Control ATM Address. There exists one Control ATM Address per MPC, therefore, the value of this entry is unique within the table. The control ATM Address is the address which is used by the MPC in its requests to the MPS. The value of this object should not change, once created.

cnLecsMpoaMpcSCSetupFrameCount.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcSCSetupFrameCount
cnLecsMpoaMpcSCSetupFrameCount.description: This represents the Short-cut setup frame count parameter. This value is frames measured over mpcSCFrameTime seconds. Flow detection is protocol independent. i.e. all network layers lecsMpcProtocolEntries for this MPC share the flow rate specification. A value of 1 causes all flows to initiate resolution/shortcut. process.

cnLecsMpoaMpcSCSetupFrameTime.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcSCSetupFrameTime
cnLecsMpoaMpcSCSetupFrameTime.description: Short-cut setup frame time, in seconds.

cnLecsMpoaMpcInitialRetryTime.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcInitialRetryTime
cnLecsMpoaMpcInitialRetryTime.description: This is the initial value for the retry time out period used for timing out MPOA Resolution Requests in seconds. Retry time consists of this initial time-out and a retry muliplier. If a response is not received, then another request is sent with a timeout of retry time * retry time maximum seconds, or until cnLecsMpoaMpcRetryTimeMaximum.

cnLecsMpoaMpcRetryTimeMaximum.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcRetryTimeMaximum
cnLecsMpoaMpcRetryTimeMaximum.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.3 MPOA Retry Mechanism
cnLecsMpoaMpcRetryTimeMaximum.description: Cumulative max value for Retry Time. Retries are attempted at intervals determined by the algorithm descrived in the definition of cnLecsMpoaMpcInitalRetryTime.

cnLecsMpoaMpcHoldDownTime.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcHoldDownTime
cnLecsMpoaMpcHoldDownTime.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.1.2.1 MPC Parameters
cnLecsMpoaMpcHoldDownTime.description: Hold Down Time Minimum time to wait before reinitiating a failed resolution attempt. Default is cnLecsMpoaMpcRetryTimeMaximum * 4.

cnLecsMpoaMpcDefaultTLV.name: cnLecsMpoaMpcDefaultTLV
cnLecsMpoaMpcDefaultTLV.description: Indicates whether this CnLecsMpoaMpcEntry contains the default TLV settings. Only one entry in the table can have the default setttings.

cnLecsMpoaMpsTable.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsTable
cnLecsMpoaMpsTable.description: The Bay Networks proprietary LECS MPS Table. This table contains configuration information for all LECS Mpoa Mpss this agent manages.

cnLecsMpoaMpsEntry.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsEntry
cnLecsMpoaMpsEntry.description: Each entry contains LECS MPS information for all LECS this agent manages.

cnLecsMpoaMpsIndex.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsIndex
cnLecsMpoaMpsIndex.description: A value which uniquely identifies this conceptual row in the cnLecsMpoaMpsTable.

cnLecsMpoaMpsRowStatus.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsRowStatus
cnLecsMpoaMpsRowStatus.description: This object allows creation and deletion of Lecs MPOA Clients. Within each conceptual cnLecsMpoaMpsTable row, writable objects may be modified, regardless of the value of cnLecsMpoaMpsRowStatus.

cnLecsMpoaMpsCtrlAtmAddr.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsCtrlAtmAddr
cnLecsMpoaMpsCtrlAtmAddr.description: The MPS's Control ATM Address. There exists one Control ATM Address per MPS, therefore, the value of this entry is unique within the table.

cnLecsMpoaMpsKeepAliveTime.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsKeepAliveTime
cnLecsMpoaMpsKeepAliveTime.description: Keep-alive time is max interval between the MPS sending MPOA Keep-Alives in seconds.

cnLecsMpoaMpsKeepAliveLifeTime.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsKeepAliveLifeTime
cnLecsMpoaMpsKeepAliveLifeTime.description: Keep-Alive Lifetime The length of time an MPC may consider a Keep-Alive valid in seconds. This value must be at least three times the cnLecsMpoaMpsKeepAliveTime.

cnLecsMpoaMpsInitialRetryTime.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsInitialRetryTime
cnLecsMpoaMpsInitialRetryTime.description: Initial value in seconds for the MPOA retry mechanism.

cnLecsMpoaMpsRetryTimeMaximum.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsRetryTimeMaximum
cnLecsMpoaMpsRetryTimeMaximum.reference: Multiprotocol Over ATM. AF-MPOA-0087.000. Section 4.3 MPOA Retry Mechanism
cnLecsMpoaMpsRetryTimeMaximum.description: Cumulative max value in seconds for Retry Time.

cnLecsMpoaMpsGiveupTime.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsGiveupTime
cnLecsMpoaMpsGiveupTime.description: Give Up Time. Minimum time in seconds to wait before giving up on a pending resolution request.

cnLecsMpoaMpsDefaultHoldingTime.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsDefaultHoldingTime
cnLecsMpoaMpsDefaultHoldingTime.description: Default Holding Time in minutes. The default Holding Time used in NHRP Resolution Replies. An egress MPS may use local information to determine a more appropriate Holding Time.

cnLecsMpoaMpsDefaultTLV.name: cnLecsMpoaMpsDefaultTLV
cnLecsMpoaMpsDefaultTLV.description: Indicates whether this CnLecsMpoaMpsEntry contains the default TLV settings. Only one entry in the table can have the default settings.
